## 2026-06-02: IDEAS

**TODO — agent-agnostic end-of-session hooks.** The token-ledger breadcrumb (S43)
is currently a manual ritual documented in every AGENT.md. Automate it as a session
hook so it fires without the agent remembering. BUT: Claude Code's settings.json
Stop/SessionEnd hooks only work for Claude — Codex, Gemini CLI, and other agents
ignore them. The Collective is LLM-agnostic, so the automation must be too.
  - Candidate: a git post-commit hook (git-level, every agent commits → agnostic).
  - Candidate: a `spells/end-session.sh` that any agent's routine invokes as the
    documented final step (single source, all agents call the same script).
  - Avoid: anything that lives only in `.claude/` — that locks it to one agent.
  Goal: end-of-session breadcrumb + log update happen the same way regardless of
  which agent ran the session.

